    <div class="recipe-idea">
        <h3>Vegetable Broth from Scraps</h3>
        <ul>
            <li><strong>Scraps to Use:</strong> Onion skins/ends, carrot peels/ends, celery ends/leaves, herb stems (parsley, cilantro), mushroom stems, leek tops.</li>
            <li><strong>Avoid:</strong> Cruciferous veggies (broccoli, cabbage, cauliflower - can make broth bitter), starchy items (potato peels - can make broth cloudy).</li>
            <li><strong>Method:</strong> Collect scraps in a bag in the freezer. When full, place in a large pot, cover with water, add peppercorns and a bay leaf. Simmer for 1-2 hours. Strain well. Use as a base for soups and sauces.</li>
        </ul>
    </div>

     <div class="recipe-idea">
        <h3>Citrus Peel Cleaner</h3>
         <ul>
            <li><strong>Scraps to Use:</strong> Orange, lemon, grapefruit peels.</li>
            <li><strong>Method:</strong> Place peels in a jar and cover with white vinegar. Let sit for 1-2 weeks, shaking occasionally. Strain the liquid into a spray bottle. Dilute with water (1:1 ratio). Use as an all-purpose cleaner (test on surfaces first, avoid natural stone).</li>
        </ul>
    </div>

     <div class="recipe-idea">
        <h3>Stale Bread Croutons/Breadcrumbs</h3>
         <ul>
            <li><strong>Scraps to Use:</strong> Stale bread (baguette, loaf ends).</li>
            <li><strong>Method (Croutons):</strong> Cut bread into cubes. Toss with olive oil, salt, pepper, herbs (optional). Bake at 180°C (350°F) until golden brown and crisp (10-15 mins).</li>
             <li><strong>Method (Breadcrumbs):</strong> Toast bread slices until very dry. Break into pieces and process in a food processor until desired crumb size. Store in an airtight container.</li>
        </ul>
    </div>

